OL,3,C'41 years after being infected with
OL,4,CHIV, I'm still fighting for justice'
OL,6,F"So my mum took me out for a drive
OL,7,Finto the countryside, which I thought
OL,8,Fwas odd because we'd never do that.
OL,10,F"I was wondering what this was for and
OL,11,FI turned to her and there were tears
OL,12,Fin her eyes.
OL,14,F"She said, 'Have you heard of HIV?'
OL,16,F"And I said, 'I've heard about it. I
OL,17,Fdon't know much about it. But I've
OL,18,Fheard it kills people.'
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G4/21
